  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter is signed by both Mrs. Mary L. Phillips and Caroline L. Phillips. They are sending a few small items for the Massachusetts Anti-Slavery fair. Their efforts to enlist the ladies of Mansfield in the preparation of a large box of gifts proved &quot;almost a perfect failure.&quot; Some preferred to give to the Connecticut fair, while &quot;others did know about the propriety of Ladies being associated with men in such a cause &amp; others were frightened at the cry of Garrison, Women rights, and Non resistance, no Government, &amp; so on.&quot;</subfield>
